bug.short_desc: Get rid of nested jars for tests

long_desc.thetext:
In order to be able to use the tycho-surefire-plugin, it would be nice to get rid of the nested jars in test bundles which confuse surefire.
Why are there some nested jars? Here is the answer from Dani (Megert): """ Almost all our (Platform, JDT, PDE) test bundles have their class files inside a JAR that's inside the JARed bundle. This is simply for historical reasons: back in the old days, each bundle was in a directory with a JAR that contained the class files. When we started to JAR most of our bundles, we converted them to have the class files directly in the bundle JAR. We did not do this for the test bundles just because there was neither a reason nor a benefit. We can accept patches that fix this, but each patch must fix all test projects inside the same repository for consistency and of course you must verify that all tests are still green before submitting the patch. """ Cf http://dev.eclipse.org/mhonarc/lists/platform-releng-dev/msg21603.html

Added link to bug 415701 which is the limitation on Tycho/Surefire side. This bug is likely to not being resolved soon since it requires changes in Maven Surefire API. So avoiding nested jars in Platform test bundles is a good workaround/solution.

I see you put this under JDT first, and then moved to releng. Unless I'm missing your point, I think it is the committers of any subproject that would have to change their test bundle. Its fine if you want to use this as an "umbrella" bug ... and clone it to specific components where you see nested jars ... but, I don't think there is anything in releng I need to do. Let me know if I'm misunderstanding.
I've put that here because it is a non-functional issue related to execution of surefire tests. But we'll indeed use this as an umbrella bug and open a bug for each component..
I think this was an umbrella bug, as all dependent bugs are closed I also mark this as closed. Please reopen if you need to do more work here.
